President Trump announced the revival of the National Space Council, which has been dormant for almost 25 years. The council will be chaired by Vice President Pence and will include representatives from various government agencies. The goal of the council is to secure America's future in space and restore the country's leadership in space exploration. The President emphasized the importance of space exploration for scientific discoveries, economic growth, technological advancements, and national security. The council will also seek input from scientists, innovators, and business leaders. President Trump signed an executive order to initiate this new chapter in America's space exploration.